---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
const base = import.meta.env.BASE_URL;
---

<Layout title="Social Justice & Underrepresented Communities">
  <h1>IV. Social Justice & Underrepresented Communities</h1>

  <p>
    AI tools are being deployed to uncover hidden histories and support communities whose voices
    have been marginalized in traditional archives. These projects demonstrate the potential for
    technology to serve social justice goals when developed in partnership with affected communities.
  </p>

  <h2>Communities in the Loop</h2>

  <p>
    The <strong>"Communities in the Loop"</strong> initiative represents a paradigm shift in how
    AI tools are developed for humanities research—centering the communities being studied in
    the development process.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Focus</strong>: AI tools identifying "veiled protest" in 19th-century Black newspapers</li>
    <li><strong>Method</strong>: Community-partnered development ensuring tools reflect lived experiences</li>
    <li><strong>Impact</strong>: Revealing resistance strategies that were deliberately obscured to avoid persecution</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These tools can detect coded language and subtle rhetorical strategies that human researchers
    might miss, while community involvement ensures interpretations remain grounded in historical
    and cultural context.
  </p>

  <h2>Indigenous Language Revitalization</h2>

  <p>
    AI is playing an increasingly important role in efforts to preserve and revitalize endangered
    indigenous languages, though this work must be conducted with careful attention to community
    sovereignty over linguistic resources.
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>FLAIR Initiative</strong>: Supports indigenous language documentation and learning through AI-assisted tools</li>
    <li><strong>Skobot</strong>: AI-powered language learning assistant developed for specific indigenous language communities</li>
    <li><strong>Principle</strong>: Community control over data, training, and deployment</li>
  </ul>

  <p>
    These projects demonstrate that AI can support language revitalization when developed in
    genuine partnership with language communities, respecting indigenous data sovereignty and
    self-determination.
  </p>

  <div class="mt-10 p-6 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-lg not-prose">
    <h3 class="font-serif text-lg font-semibold text-stone-800 mb-2">Key Takeaway</h3>
    <p class="text-stone-700">
      The most successful AI applications in social justice contexts are those developed
      <em>with</em> rather than <em>for</em> communities, ensuring technology serves community-defined
      goals and respects community ownership of cultural heritage.
    </p>
  </div>

  <nav class="mt-12 flex justify-between not-prose">
    <a href={`${base}archaeology/`} class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">&larr; Previous: III. Ancient Text Recovery</a>
    <a href={`${base}ethics/`} class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Next: V. Ethical Risks &rarr;</a>
  </nav>
</Layout>
